 Rice PLT Group 
Rice Programming Language Research 
The Programming Language Theory (PLT) Group at Rice works on all
aspects of advanced programming languages, including design,
semantics, implementations, programming environment tools, and
applications. 
We are developing DrScheme, a comprehensive programming environment
for writing, debugging and analyzing Scheme programs.
  DrScheme Programming Environment
  On-Line Documentation
  Publications
  Software Packages
  PLT People
Contacting us:
Regarding problems with our software, write to
plt-bugs@cs.rice.edu.
For general information, write us at
scheme@cs.rice.edu.